(80, 1, '2018-03-25 06:03:45', '2018-03-25 06:03:45', 'So what‚Äôs the deal with Japan‚Äôs Yuzuru Hanyu and all those Winnie-the-Pooh dolls at the Winter Olympics?\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter wp-image-81 \" src=\"http://localhost/WING-Emily-WORDPRESS/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/featureImg06-300x169.jpg\" alt=\"Yuzuru and Pooh Chaos\" width=\"430\" height=\"242\" />\r\n\r\nAfter completing his Olympic programs, the crowd at Gangneung Ice Arena made it rain. The skating surface was littered with Pooh dolls, all the better to pay tribute to the now double Olympic gold medalist and 2017 world champion.\r\n\r\nSimply put, Winnie the Pooh is kind of Hanyu‚Äôs thing. The 23-year-old, a heartthrob in his home country of Japan, began carrying around a tissue box in 2010 that was embedded in A.A. Milne‚Äôs beloved character.\r\n\r\nWhen Hanyu skated, he would arrange his Pooh Bear to make sure it had a good view of him, and he brought it with him to news conferences. Eventually, his association with the doll took on a life of its own, and even though Olympic sponsorship rules reportedly forbid his furry¬†friend from accompanying him to the rink, fans make sure Hanyu does not suffer from a Pooh deficiency.\r\n\r\nAt other competitions, Pooh has been placed next to Hanyu‚Äôs coach, Brian Orser, who won 1984 and 1988 Olympic silver medals for Canada. ‚ÄúYou go backstage, and there are bags and bags and bags,‚Äù Orser said in 2016 of the dolls that fans hurl toward Hanyu, who donates them to children in the area surrounding whatever arena hosted the shower ‚Äî in this case, Gangneung and PyeongChang.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/early-lead/wp/2018/02/16/so-whats-the-deal-with-japans-yuzuru-hanyu-and-all-those-winnie-the-pooh-dolls/?utm_term=.69a04a8626e1\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Reference</a>', 'Yuzuru and Winnie the Pooh', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'yuzuru-and-winnie-the-pooh__trashed', '', '', '2018-04-22 02:18:21', '2018-